RIYADH: Saudi Arabia announced two deaths from COVID-19 and 29 new infections on Saturday. Of the new cases, nine were recorded in Riyadh, seven inÂ  Jeddah, three in Makkah, two in Taif, and two in Dhahran. Several other cities recorded one new case each. The total number of recoveries in the Kingdom increased to 539,011 after 21 more patients recovered from the virus. A total of 8,842 people have succumbed to the virus in the Kingdom so far. Over 47.6 million doses of a coronavirus vaccine have been administered in the Kingdom to date.